data.enText: to come together in a group

data.chText: 年轻人傍晚时经常聚集在大广场上。
data.enText: Young people often congregate in the main square in the evenings.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 表加强 + greg 集合 + ate 表动词 → 集合到一起 → 聚集

tr: come together, usually for a purpose
example: The crowds congregated in front of the Vatican on Christmas Eve

value.def: When people congregate, they gather together and form a group.

example.ex: Youngsters love to congregate here in the evenings outside cinemas showing American films...
example.tran: 晚上，年轻人喜欢聚集在放映美国电影的电影院外面。

example.ex: Visitors congregated on Sunday afternoons to view public exhibitions.
example.tran: 每周日下午，游客成群结队地来看公开展览。
